Pseudocode:
Algorithm minFinder is
input: Integer Array arr
output: Integer index
int index equals 0
int min equals Array arr at element 0
for int i=0 until i is smaller than Array arr length
if arr at i is smaller than int min do
int min equals Array arr at i
int index equals i
increment i
return int index


Pseudocode:
Algorithm minFinder_recursive is
input: Integer Array arr
Integer min
Integer minIndex
Integer currentIndex
output: minFinder_recursive algorithm recursively
Integer minIndex
if currentIndex equals Array arr length minus 1
return int minIndex
if int min is bigger than Array arr at element currentIndex
int min equals Array arr at element currentIndex
int minIndex equals int currentIndex
return algorithm minFinder_recursive recursively
